adjectives.description: contaminated (comparative more contaminated, superlative most contaminated)

entries.meaning: made unfit for use by the introduction of unwholesome or undesirable elements.
examples: A "contaminated" runway has over 25% of its surface area covered with standing water or slush (or loose snow) more than 3mm thick, or compressed snow and ice anywhere along the takeoff run or accelerate-stop surface.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of contaminate
